The simple Present Tense
We use simple present tense for:
- Habits or daily routines
She gets up at eight o'clock every day.
- Permanent states
They live in Turkey
General truths or laws of nature
The sun rises in the east
Water boils at 100 degrees Celsius.

Wh - Questions
Formula: Wh - word + do / does + Subject + Verb?

Ex:
Where do you live?
Why do you learn English?
When does he arrive home?
